#: ../../../doc/en/example/pythoncollection.rst:2
msgid "Changing standard (Python) test discovery"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/example/pythoncollection.rst:5
msgid "Ignore paths during test collection"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/example/pythoncollection.rst:7
msgid ""
"You can easily ignore certain test directories and modules during collection "
"by passing the ``--ignore=path`` option on the cli. ``pytest`` allows "
"multiple ``--ignore`` options. Example::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/example/pythoncollection.rst:11
msgid ""
"tests/\n"
"|-- example\n"
"|   |-- test_example_01.py\n"
"|   |-- test_example_02.py\n"
"|   '-- test_example_03.py\n"
"|-- foobar\n"
"|   |-- test_foobar_01.py\n"
"|   |-- test_foobar_02.py\n"
"|   '-- test_foobar_03.py\n"
"'-- hello\n"
"    '-- world\n"
"        |-- test_world_01.py\n"
"        |-- test_world_02.py\n"
"        '-- test_world_03.py"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/example/pythoncollection.rst:26
msgid ""
"Now if you invoke ``pytest`` with ``--ignore=tests/foobar/test_foobar_03.py "
"--ignore=tests/hello/``, you will see that ``pytest`` only collects test-"
"modules, which do not match the patterns specified::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/example/pythoncollection.rst:29
msgid ""
"========= test session starts ==========\n"
"platform darwin -- Python 2.7.10, pytest-2.8.2, py-1.4.30, pluggy-0.3.1\n"
"rootdir: $REGENDOC_TMPDIR, inifile:\n"
"collected 5 items\n"
"\n"
"tests/example/test_example_01.py .\n"
"tests/example/test_example_02.py .\n"
"tests/example/test_example_03.py .\n"
"tests/foobar/test_foobar_01.py .\n"
"tests/foobar/test_foobar_02.py .\n"
"\n"
"======= 5 passed in 0.02 seconds ======="
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/example/pythoncollection.rst:44
msgid "Changing directory recursion"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/example/pythoncollection.rst:46
msgid ""
"You can set the :confval:`norecursedirs` option in an ini-file, for example "
"your ``setup.cfg`` in the project root directory::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/example/pythoncollection.rst:48
msgid ""
"# content of setup.cfg\n"
"[pytest]\n"
"norecursedirs = .svn _build tmp*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/example/pythoncollection.rst:52
msgid ""
"This would tell ``pytest`` to not recurse into typical subversion or sphinx-"
"build directories or into any ``tmp`` prefixed directory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/example/pythoncollection.rst:57
msgid "Changing naming conventions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/example/pythoncollection.rst:59
msgid ""
"You can configure different naming conventions by setting the :confval:"
"`python_files`, :confval:`python_classes` and :confval:`python_functions` "
"configuration options.  Example::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/example/pythoncollection.rst:63
msgid ""
"# content of setup.cfg\n"
"# can also be defined in in tox.ini or pytest.ini file\n"
"[pytest]\n"
"python_files=check_*.py\n"
"python_classes=Check\n"
"python_functions=*_check"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/example/pythoncollection.rst:70
msgid ""
"This would make ``pytest`` look for tests in files that match the ``check_* ."
"py`` glob-pattern, ``Check`` prefixes in classes, and functions and methods "
"that match ``*_check``.  For example, if we have::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/example/pythoncollection.rst:74
msgid ""
"# content of check_myapp.py\n"
"class CheckMyApp:\n"
"    def simple_check(self):\n"
"        pass\n"
"    def complex_check(self):\n"
"        pass"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/example/pythoncollection.rst:81
msgid "then the test collection looks like this::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/example/pythoncollection.rst:83
msgid ""
"$ py.test --collect-only\n"
"======= test session starts ========\n"
"platform linux -- Python 3.5.1, pytest-2.9.2, py-1.4.31, pluggy-0.3.1\n"
"rootdir: $REGENDOC_TMPDIR, inifile: setup.cfg\n"
"collected 2 items\n"
"<Module 'check_myapp.py'>\n"
"  <Class 'CheckMyApp'>\n"
"    <Instance '()'>\n"
"      <Function 'simple_check'>\n"
"      <Function 'complex_check'>\n"
"\n"
"======= no tests ran in 0.12 seconds ========"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/example/pythoncollection.rst:98
msgid ""
"the ``python_functions`` and ``python_classes`` options has no effect for "
"``unittest.TestCase`` test discovery because pytest delegates detection of "
"test case methods to unittest code."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/example/pythoncollection.rst:103
msgid "Interpreting cmdline arguments as Python packages"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/example/pythoncollection.rst:105
msgid ""
"You can use the ``--pyargs`` option to make ``pytest`` try interpreting "
"arguments as python package names, deriving their file system path and then "
"running the test. For example if you have unittest2 installed you can type::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/example/pythoncollection.rst:110
msgid "py.test --pyargs unittest2.test.test_skipping -q"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/example/pythoncollection.rst:112
msgid ""
"which would run the respective test module.  Like with other options, "
"through an ini-file and the :confval:`addopts` option you can make this "
"change more permanently::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/example/pythoncollection.rst:116
msgid ""
"# content of pytest.ini\n"
"[pytest]\n"
"addopts = --pyargs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/example/pythoncollection.rst:120
msgid ""
"Now a simple invocation of ``py.test NAME`` will check if NAME exists as an "
"importable package/module and otherwise treat it as a filesystem path."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/example/pythoncollection.rst:125
msgid "Finding out what is collected"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/example/pythoncollection.rst:127
msgid ""
"You can always peek at the collection tree without running tests like this::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/example/pythoncollection.rst:129
msgid ""
". $ py.test --collect-only pythoncollection.py\n"
"======= test session starts ========\n"
"platform linux -- Python 3.5.1, pytest-2.9.2, py-1.4.31, pluggy-0.3.1\n"
"rootdir: $REGENDOC_TMPDIR, inifile: pytest.ini\n"
"collected 3 items\n"
"<Module 'CWD/pythoncollection.py'>\n"
"  <Function 'test_function'>\n"
"  <Class 'TestClass'>\n"
"    <Instance '()'>\n"
"      <Function 'test_method'>\n"
"      <Function 'test_anothermethod'>\n"
"\n"
"======= no tests ran in 0.12 seconds ========"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/example/pythoncollection.rst:144
msgid "customizing test collection to find all .py files"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/example/pythoncollection.rst:148
msgid ""
"You can easily instruct ``pytest`` to discover tests from every python file::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/example/pythoncollection.rst:151
msgid ""
"# content of pytest.ini\n"
"[pytest]\n"
"python_files = *.py"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/example/pythoncollection.rst:155
msgid ""
"However, many projects will have a ``setup.py`` which they don't want to be "
"imported. Moreover, there may files only importable by a specific python "
"version. For such cases you can dynamically define files to be ignored by "
"listing them in a ``conftest.py`` file::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/example/pythoncollection.rst:159
msgid ""
"# content of conftest.py\n"
"import sys\n"
"\n"
"collect_ignore = [\"setup.py\"]\n"
"if sys.version_info[0] > 2:\n"
"    collect_ignore.append(\"pkg/module_py2.py\")"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/example/pythoncollection.rst:166
msgid "And then if you have a module file like this::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/example/pythoncollection.rst:168
msgid ""
"# content of pkg/module_py2.py\n"
"def test_only_on_python2():\n"
"    try:\n"
"        assert 0\n"
"    except Exception, e:\n"
"        pass"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/example/pythoncollection.rst:175
msgid "and a setup.py dummy file like this::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/example/pythoncollection.rst:177
msgid ""
"# content of setup.py\n"
"0/0  # will raise exception if imported"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/example/pythoncollection.rst:180
msgid ""
"then a pytest run on Python2 will find the one test and will leave out the "
"setup.py file::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/example/pythoncollection.rst:183
msgid ""
"#$ py.test --collect-only\n"
"====== test session starts ======\n"
"platform linux2 -- Python 2.7.10, pytest-2.9.1, py-1.4.31, pluggy-0.3.1\n"
"rootdir: $REGENDOC_TMPDIR, inifile: pytest.ini\n"
"collected 1 items\n"
"<Module 'pkg/module_py2.py'>\n"
"  <Function 'test_only_on_python2'>\n"
"\n"
"====== no tests ran in 0.04 seconds ======"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/example/pythoncollection.rst:193
msgid ""
"If you run with a Python3 interpreter both the one test and the setup.py "
"file will be left out::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/example/pythoncollection.rst:196
msgid ""
"$ py.test --collect-only\n"
"======= test session starts ========\n"
"platform linux -- Python 3.5.1, pytest-2.9.2, py-1.4.31, pluggy-0.3.1\n"
"rootdir: $REGENDOC_TMPDIR, inifile: pytest.ini\n"
"collected 0 items\n"
"\n"
"======= no tests ran in 0.12 seconds ========"
msgstr ""
